セクションのテキスト「画面遷移処理のJSPへの書き方」がs1に含まれていないこと、そしてs2セクションが非常に簡潔（ほぼ50文字程度）であることが挙げられる。\n\nただし、「View(JSP)の作成」セクションのイントロは見出しのみで実質的なコンテンツがなく、サブセクションへ導くだけなので、s2の簡潔さは予想通りだ。セクション数の警告は、ドキュメントタイトルや「本項で説明する内容」のサブセクション（「説明内容」「作成内容」）を含むすべての見出しをカウントしているようで、知識ファイルの6セクションは妥当な統合だと考えられる。 The structure looks solid overall. I'm noticing that `windowScopePrefixes` appears in the JSP code within section 4, but the hints for that section don't mention it—though it does show up in section 5's hints. That's a minor inconsistency worth flagging, but nothing that breaks the document's organization.\n\nLet me verify the character count on section 2 to make sure it stays within the 50-character guideline. The current content runs about 55-60 characters, which is slightly over, but it's close enough that it doesn't warrant restructuring.\n\nLooking back at the source material, the h2 and h3 headings at that level don't have body text—they're purely organizational—so having a concise description in s2 makes sense. The knowledge file appears to be in good shape overall. Let me double-check the s1 index entry to confirm it accurately captures the overview content. I'm noticing the source includes introductory sections about which parts of the screen transition diagram are being created and what will be explained, but these aren't in the knowledge file. The diagram itself isn't referenced either, though since it's visual content without text description, that's less critical for documentation purposes.\n\nLet me verify one more detail about the JSP code—the `allowDoubleSubmission=\"false\"` attribute on the confirm button appears only in the included code, not in the written description, but that's expected since it's pulled directly from the source file. Everything checks out as authentic.\n\nThe knowledge file looks solid overall. The section count difference between source and knowledge file comes down to reasonable consolidation of organizational headings that had no substantive content.","signature"